The article is a transcript of a speech given by President Biden at a private residence in Los Angeles, California. In his speech, President Biden thanks his wife, Jill Biden, and praises her for her role as First Lady. He also acknowledges the support and contributions of Nancy Pelosi, Kamala Harris, Karen Bass, and Gavin Newsom. The President expresses gratitude to the hosts and attendees of the event for their support. He highlights the achievements of his administration, including job creation, economic growth, and rebuilding alliances. President Biden emphasizes the importance of democracy and criticizes former President Trump for his actions and statements that threaten democracy. He calls on the American people to protect and strengthen democracy and expresses optimism about the future of the country. The President concludes his speech by affirming the resilience and capacity of the United States.